# Scripts in scripts/

All project scripts (e.g. `.ps1`, `.sh`, build and utility scripts) must live in the **`scripts/`** folder at the project root.

## Rules

- **New scripts:** Create or add scripts only under `scripts/` (e.g. `scripts/build-booking-zip.ps1`, `scripts/cleanup-plugin-zips.ps1`).
- **Invocation:** Run from project root with `.\scripts\<script-name>` (e.g. `.\scripts\sync-chameleon-standards.ps1`).
- **References:** In docs and rules, point to `scripts/` (e.g. "Run `.\scripts\build-booking-zip.ps1`").

## Reminder

When adding or documenting a script, place it in `scripts/` and refer to it as `scripts/<name>`.
